article.headline: Evansville 86, NC A&amp,T 65
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. -- Colt Ryan scored 29 points and Evansville used an accurate shooting effort for an 86-65 victory over North Carolina A&T on Saturday night. Evansville (4-4) was strong in each shooting category -- 49 percent from the floor, 63.2 percent from 3-point range and 92.9 percent from the free-throw line. Ryan, a guard, made 5 of 7 from long range and was perfect in 10 trips to the foul line. Evansville had three other players score in double figures -- Kenny Harris (13), Ned Cox (12) and Denver Holmes (10). North Carolina A&T (4-5) was led by Adrian Powell's 15 points, including 6 of 6 from the floor, including a pair of 3-pointers.Marc Hill added 12 points. North Carolina A&T had a big 38-22 rebounding advantage, led by DaMetrius Upchurch's eight.
